            "message": "Field [budgetRefs] cannot be null or empty.",
            "detail": "Field error in object statusUpdateRequestModel on field budgetRefs: rejected value [null].",
            "level": "Request Error"
        }
    ],
    "timestamp": "2024-04-01T06:33:59.480+0000"
} For missing or empty  active : {
    "id": "c10c5651-6253-492a-ab67-4259b09c4a09",
    "status": "400",
    "title": "Bad Request",
    "errors": [
        {
            "code": "400",
            "element": "active",
            "message": "Field [active] cannot be null or empty. Possible values: [true/false]",
            "detail": "Field error in object 'statusUpdateRequestModel' on field 'active': rejected value [null]",
            "level": "Field Error"
        }
    ],
    "timestamp": "2024-04-02T18:54:02.994+0000"
} Upon submission, the endpoint should accept the request and return an asynchronous response. Additionally, specific validation messages must be included in case of invalid  budgetRefs  or non-existent reference values within the system. For invalid  budgetRefs : "status" : "FAILED",
"errors" : [ 
      {
          "code" : "404",
          "element" : "budgetRef",
          "message" : "Field [budgetRef] cannot be null or empty. At least one of the Field [id, externalId, docNo] should have a value.",
          "detail" : "Field error in object budgetRefModel on field budgetRefs: rejected value [ReferenceModel(id=null, externalId=null, docNo=null, label=null, type=null, archived =false)].",
          "level" : "Field Error"
      }
  ]   For non-existent reference values in  budgetRefs : "status" : "FAILED",
"errors" : [ 
      {
          "code" : "400",
          "element" : "docNo",
          "message" : "No [budget] record found.",
          "detail" : "Budget referenced by [docNo] not found. Provided value: [AD-1-111].",
          "level" : "Field Error"
      }
  ] Furthermore, before updating the budget status from  Inactive  to  Active , the endpoint must perform additional validations: Validate the duration dates ( fromDate  &  toDate ). If  fromDate  is in the future, updating the catalog status should be disallowed, and a validation error should be added against the budget reference with the status  FAILED . "status" : "FAILED",
"errors" : [ 
    {
        "code" : "400",
        "element" : "docNo",
        "message" : "This budget cannot be activated since the start date is in the future.",
        "detail" : "This budget cannot be activated since the start date is in the future. Current start date: [yyyy-MM-dd]",
        "level" : "Field Error"
    }
] If the  toDate  is in the past, a validation message should be added against that reference with the status  FAILED . "status" : "FAILED",
"errors" : [ 
    {
        "code" : "400",
        "element" : "docNo",
        "message" : "This budget cannot be activated since the budget duration has expired.",
        "detail" : "This budget cannot be activated since the budget duration has expired. Please update budget duration to activate this budget.",
        "level" : "Field Error"
    }
] If the budget is already active, a warning message with the status UNCHANGED should be provided: "status" : "UNCHANGED",
"warnings" : [
    {
        "code" : "400",
        "element" : "docNo",
        "message" : "This [budget] is already active.",
        "detail" : "The [budget] referenced by [docNo] is already active. No update performed.",
        "level" : "Field Error"
    }
] Similarly, before updating the budget status from  Active  to  Inactive , the following validation should be performed:  If the budget is already inactive, the status should be UNCHANGED with a warning message. "status" : "UNCHANGED",
"warnings" : [
    {
        "code" : "400",
        "element" : "docNo",
        "message" : "This budget is already inactive.",
        "detail" : "The budget referenced by [docNo] is already inactive. No update performed.",
        "level" : "Field Error"
    }
] Note : All Budgets in SUCCESS Status in processingResult: If all budgets included in the request have a status of  SUCCESS , the header-level status of the asynchronous request should be  COMPLETED . Some Budgets in FAILED Status in processingResult: If there are budgets in the request that have a status of  FAILED , while others might be in  SUCCESS  status, the header-level status should be  COMPLETED_WITH_FAILURE . All Budgets in UN_CHANGED Status in processingResult: If all budgets in the request have a status of UNCHANGED, indicating that no changes were made, the header-level status should be  COMPLETED_WITH_WARNING . Mixed Statuses in processingResult: If the  processingResult  contains both  FAILED  and UNCHANGED statuses, indicating a mixture of failed and unchanged budgets, the header-level status should be  COMPLETED_WITH_FAILURE . System-Level Failure: In case of a system-level failure unrelated to individual budget statuses, the header-level status should be  ERROR . This indicates an issue preventing the processing of the request at the system level. Endpoint:  POST /budgets/status-update/async Request Body: {
  "budgetRefs": [
    {
      "id": "561234cdeacb256789aa",
      "externalId": "11001",
      "docNo": "CC01"
    }
  ],
